Package uk.ac.bris.cs.scotlandyard.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Ai
    All CPU (Ai) players should implement this interface and be on the classpath.
    Board
    Represents the ScotlandYard game board
    Board.GameState
    Represents an on-going ScotlandYard game where moves by each player advances the game.
    Board.TicketBoard
    Represents the ScotlandYard ticket board for each player
    Model
    The game model of ScotlandYard game.
    Model.Observer
    An observer of the ScotlandYard game.
    Move
    Represents a move in the ScotlandYard game.
    Move.Visitor<T>
    A generic visitor for use with the Move.visit(Visitor) method.
    Piece
    Represent a colored counter in the ScotlandYard game
    ScotlandYard.Factory<T>
    A generic factory used to create a game state or model
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GameSetup
    A POJO containing the ScotlandYard game graph and the MrX's reveal rounds
    ImmutableBoard
    A POJO representing an immutable game board.
    LogEntry
    A POJO representing log entries of the MrX's travel log.
    ModelFactories
    Not part of the coursework, required for the tests to find your factory implementations.
    Move.DoubleMove
    A POJO representing a double move with two tickets
    Move.FunctionalVisitor<T>
    A visitor adapter that takes two Functions and turn them into visitors.
    Move.SingleMove
    A POJO representing a single move with one ticket
    MyGameStateFactory
    cw-model Stage 1: Complete this class
    MyModelFactory
    cw-model Stage 2: Complete this class
    Player
    A POJO representing an immutable player of the ScotlandYard game.
    ScotlandYard
    A utility class containing things needed for the ScotlandYard game
